    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.Fim0r8kwu9pO2qPe]{Weapon Group: Small Arms, Two-Handed}&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Very similar to a normal sonic weapon, the sonic stunner is designed only to be non-lethal. Some variations of other sonic weapons incorporate this configuration as an adjustable switch (though they are commensurately more expensive).<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A target hit by a sonic stunner must make a DC20 Constitution saving throw or increase its exhaustion level by +1 (to a maximum of level 5) for 1 minute. Unlike normal exhaustion, levels incurred by this weapon reduce by 1 every minute after suffering the last attack from it.</span></p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sonic stunner </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">4,5000 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Special thunder </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">50/200 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">5 lb. </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reload (5-M), TL3</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.4w8qhwBphOalJ7Z8]{Sonic}&nbsp;@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.exbZomqY2kQVhvmP]{Sonic Stunner}&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.QjoW3JNAsq3eJt4s]{Reload 5-M} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-equipment.lmAMoPPYbIwgHfGl]{Battry Cell, Medium}</p>",
